Kiro'o Studio is the first game development in Central Africa. The Studio started as a start up
idea by Madiba Olivier in 2002. The studio aim is to unify and distribute African culture by
combining various myths, folktales and traditional African values into the gaming industry.
In an interview, Mr Madiba indicated the growing concern of youth unemployment in the
continent. He hopes to give an opportunity to hardworking youth to be part of the Kiro'o
mission. Madiba is also an experience programmer and believes that the best developer in the
world are the ones which are always ready to share their work for constructive critisicm.
Until now, Kiro'o has almost 20 employees who are working together to produce "sAurion:
Legacy of the Kori-Odan". This is an action RPG game based on Ghana history of kingship.
